                    "comment": "kszucs commented on PR #13511:\nURL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/13511#issuecomment-1173907392\n\n   > @kszucs this is one of the improvements we discussed in the past. I only have one question at this point, should we run this PR/command after submitting binaries instead of after submitting sources?\r\n   \r\n   I'd prefer submitting two jobs: one after the source tarball is available and another one after we uploaded the binaries. This would help to catch problems with the source release even before the binary builds finish.\r\n   \r\n   > In the case we want to do it after submitting sources we probably want to change the github comment to not trigger binaries and wheels yet, right? only sources?\r\n   \r\n   Correct. \r\n   \r\n   \n\n\n",
